Sentencas: The neodymium-deficient nickelate Nd(1.95)NiO(4+delta) mixed conducting K(2)NiF(4)-type oxide, was evaluated as cathode for solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Neodymium-deficient nickelate oxide Nd1.95NiO4+δ as cathode material for anode-supported intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrochemical properties were investigated on planar Ni-YSZ anode-supported SOFC based on co-tape casted and co-fired HTceramix (R) cells.
Titulo: Neodymium-deficient nickelate oxide Nd1.95NiO4+δ as cathode material for anode-supported intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Using a layer of strontium doped lanthanum cobaltite as current collector, a current density of 1.31 A cm(-2) (at 0.70V) was obtained at 800 degrees C using hydrogen fuel with small single cells, after optimizing the cathode sintering temperature.
Titulo: Neodymium-deficient nickelate oxide Nd1.95NiO4+δ as cathode material for anode-supported intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Impedance spectroscopy measurements were performed: the different resistive contributions and the values of the corresponding equivalent capacities are discussed.
Titulo: Neodymium-deficient nickelate oxide Nd1.95NiO4+δ as cathode material for anode-supported intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
